    "course_title": "FUNCTIONAL NEUROANATOMY FOR PHYSICAL THERAPY",
    "description": "Development, structure, regions and function of the nervous system are covered with the purpose of providing insight into the clinical treatment of common neurological conditions. General principles of the development, connectivity and blood supply of both the central and peripheral nervous system (spinal cord, brainstem, and above the brainstem) are taught.",
